<eesti>K&uuml;tuse- ja energiamajanduse &uuml;ldkorraldus </eesti>
<inglise>General Organisation of Fuel and Energy Sector </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. (Kehtetu - 11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. (Repealed - 11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Vedelk&uuml;tuste kvaliteedin&otilde;uded ja n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamine </eesti>
<inglise>Quality requirements for and certification of conformity of liquid fuels </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vedelk&uuml;tuste kvaliteedin&otilde;uded kehtestatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Quality requirements for liquid fuels shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>Kvaliteedin&otilde;uded kehtestatakse ainult m&auml;&auml;ruses nimetatud k&uuml;tustele. </eesti>
<inglise>Quality requirements shall be established only for fuels specified in the regulation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vedelk&uuml;tuse vastavust kehtestatud kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele t&otilde;endatakse volitatud asutuse poolt v&auml;ljaantud vedelk&uuml;tuse vastavussertifikaadiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Conformity of liquid fuel with the established quality requirements shall be attested by a certificate of conformity of liquid fuel issued by an approved body. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastavussertifikaadi vormi ja v&auml;ljaandmise korra kehtestab majandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The format of and procedure for the issue of certificates of conformity shall be established by the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volitatud asutus k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on isik, kellele k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud korras on antud &otilde;igus tegutseda vedelk&uuml;tuse sertifitseerimiseks volitatud asutusena. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For the purposes of this Act, "approved body" means a person who is granted, pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsection (4) of this section, the right to operate as a body approved to certify liquid fuel. </inglise>
<eesti>Volitatud asutusena tegutsemise &otilde;iguse v&otilde;ib anda vedelk&uuml;tuse sertifitseerimiseks akrediteeritud asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The right to operate as an approved body may be granted to bodies accredited to certify liquid fuel. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Isikule vedelk&uuml;tuse sertifitseerimiseks volitatud asutusena tegutsemise &otilde;iguse andmise, volitatud asutusena tegutsemise, tema &uuml;le riikliku j&auml;relevalve korraldamise ja tegutsemis&otilde;iguse &auml;rav&otilde;tmise korral kohaldatakse toote n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamise seaduse (RT I 1999, 92, 825; RT I 2002, 6, 20) s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Provisions of the Product Conformity Attestation Act (RT I 1999, 92, 825; RT I 2002, 6, 20) apply to the grant of the right to operate as a body approved to certify liquid fuel to persons, operation as an approved body, organisation of state supervision over approved bodies and deprivation of the right to operate as an approved body. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Otilde;igus tegutseda vedelk&uuml;tuse sertifitseerimiseks volitatud asutusena antakse t&auml;htajaliselt kuni viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The right to operate as a body approved to certify liquid fuel is granted for a term of up to five years. </inglise>
<eesti>Volitatud asutus peab tagama tema poolt tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamise. </eesti>
<inglise>An approved body shall guarantee compensation for damage caused by the approved body. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Vedelk&uuml;tuse importimisel on importija kohustatud esitama tollile vedelk&uuml;tuse vastavussertifikaadi. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon importation of liquid fuel, the importer is required to submit the certificate of conformity of liquid fuel to the customs authorities. </inglise>
<eesti>Kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele mittevastava vedelk&uuml;tuse import, ladustamine ja m&uuml;&uuml;k on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>Import, storage and sale of liquid fuel which does not comply with quality requirements is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastavussertifikaadita on lubatud k&uuml;tust importida k&uuml;tuseaktsiisi seaduses (RT I 1993, 38, 563; RT I 1996, 90, 1613; 1997, 73, 1201; 77, 1314; 86, 1464; 1998, 57, 862; 1999, 10, 158; 2000, 33, 199; 59, 380; 2001, 88, 531) s&auml;testatud maksuvabas koguses. </eesti>
<inglise>Fuel without a certificate of conformity may be imported in the tax-free quantity established in the Fuel Excise Duty Act (RT I 1993, 38, 563; RT I 1996, 90, 1613; 1997, 73, 1201; 77, 1314; 86, 1464; 1998, 57, 862; 1999, 10, 158; 2000, 33, 199; 59, 380; 2001, 88, 531). </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Vedelk&uuml;tuse tootja, t&ouml;&ouml;tleja, ladustaja v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;ja on kohustatud j&auml;relevalveasutuse n&otilde;udmisel esitama oma valduses oleva vedelk&uuml;tuse vastavussertifikaadi ja v&otilde;imaldama vedelk&uuml;tuse vastavuse kontrollimist kehtestatud kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Producers, refiners, storers and sellers of liquid fuel are required to present the certificate of conformity of liquid fuel in their possession at the request of the supervisory agency and to allow verification of conformity of liquid fuel with the established quality requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. (Kehtetu - 11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. (Repealed - 11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. (Kehtetu - 10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. (Repealed - 10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. (Kehtetu - 11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. (Repealed - 11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Undertakings with a valid activity licence have tK&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tegevusaladel tegutsemise &otilde;igus on ettev&otilde;tjal, kellel on kehtiv tegevusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Undertakings with a valid activity licence have the right to operate in the areas of activity specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba on n&otilde;utav j&auml;rgmistel tegevusaladel: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An activity licence is required in the following areas of activity: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&uuml;tuse import ja m&uuml;&uuml;k; </eesti>
<inglise>1) import and sale of fuel; </inglise>
<eesti>2) elektrienergia eksport, import ja m&uuml;&uuml;k; </eesti>
<inglise>2) export, import and sale of electric power; </inglise>
<eesti>3) soojusenergia m&uuml;&uuml;k; </eesti>
<inglise>3) sale of thermal power; </inglise>
<eesti>4) energia, vedelk&uuml;tuse ja gaasi edastamis- ning jaotamisteenuse m&uuml;&uuml;k v&otilde;rgu kaudu; </eesti>
<inglise>4) sale of transmission or transport and distribution services for energy, liquid fuel and gas through networks; </inglise>
<eesti>5) elektri-, soojus- ja gaasis&uuml;steemi operatiivjuhtimise teenuse m&uuml;&uuml;k. </eesti>
<inglise>5) sale of operational management services for electric power, heat, and network gas systems. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloaks on t&auml;htajaline turuluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An activity licence is a market licence issued for a specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>Turuluba antakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 1 nimetatud tegevusteks t&auml;htajaga kuni viis aastat ja punktides 2-5 nimetatud tegevusteks t&auml;htajaga kuni 12 aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>Market licences are issued for a term of up to five years for activities specified in clause (2) 1) and for a term of up to twelve years for activities specified in clauses (2) 2) -5) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3 (1)) Turuloata on lubatud k&uuml;tust importida k&uuml;tuseaktsiisi seaduses s&auml;testatud maksuvabas koguses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3 (1)) Fuel may be imported without a market licence in the tax-free quantity established in the Fuel Excise Duty Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) F&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, kes ei t&auml;ida energia tootmise, edastamise v&otilde;i jaotamise funktsioone ning kes k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 14 l&otilde;ikes 1 (1) nimetatud seadmeid, elektriliine v&otilde;i torustikku kasutades ostab ja m&uuml;&uuml;b energiat ainult oma aktsion&auml;ridele, osanikele, liikmetele, rentnikele v&otilde;i &uuml;&uuml;rnikele, ei vaja turuluba, kui energiam&uuml;&uuml;k ei ole tema p&otilde;hitegevusala. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Natural or legal persons, who do not perform the functions of energy production, transmission or distribution and who, using the equipment, power lines or pipelines specified in subsection 14 (1 (1)) of this Act, only buy energy for and sell it to their shareholders, members, commercial lessees or tenants, do not need a market licence if the sale of energy is not the principal activity of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turuloa annab Energiaturu Inspektsioon turuluba taotleva ettev&otilde;tja (edaspidi taotleja) taotluse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A market licence is issued by the Energy Market Inspectorate on the basis of an application from an undertaking applying for a market licence (hereinafter applicant). </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Turuluba antakse &auml;riregistrisse kantud v&otilde;i asutamisel olevale &auml;ri&uuml;hingule v&otilde;i &auml;riregistrisse kantud v&auml;lismaa &auml;ri&uuml;hingu filiaalile, kui tal on tehnilised v&otilde;imalused ja vajaliku oskusega personal tegutsemiseks taotluses m&auml;rgitud tegevusalal ning tema tegevus vastab keskkonnakaitse, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja muudele &otilde;igusaktidega etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A market licence shall be issued to a company entered in the commercial register or being founded or to the branch of a foreign company entered in the commercial register if the company has the technical capability and personnel with the necessary skills to operate in the area of activity indicated in the application and if its activities comply with the environmental protection and occupational safety requirements and other requirements prescribed by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Turuloa vormi kehtestab majandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The format of the market licence shall be established by the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Turuloa andmise eest v&otilde;etakse riigil&otilde;ivu vastavalt riigil&otilde;ivuseadusele (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; RT I 2001, 55, 331; 56, 332; 64, 367; 65, 377; 85, 512; 88, 531; 91, 543; 93, 565; 2002, 1, 1; 18, 97; 23, 131; 24, 135). </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A state fee is charged for the issue of a market licence pursuant to the State Fees Act (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; RT I 2001, 55, 331; 56, 332; 64, 367; 65, 377; 85, 512; 88, 531; 91, 543; 93, 565; 2002, 1, 1; 18, 97; 23, 131; 24, 135). </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Turuloa taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for market licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuloa saamiseks esitab taotleja Energiaturu Inspektsioonile taotluse, milles on v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to be issued a market licence, the applicant shall submit an application to the Energy Market Inspectorate containing at least the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tja &auml;rinimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the business name of the undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asukoha aadress ja tegevuskoht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the address of the seat and place of business; </inglise>
<eesti>3) sidevahendite numbrid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the telecommunications numbers; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &auml;riregistri kood; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the commercial registry code; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tegevusalad vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikele 2. </eesti>
<inglise>5) areas of activity according to subsection 9 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud taotlusele lisatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following shall be appended to an application specified in subsection (1) of this section: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &auml;riregistri registrikaardi &auml;rakiri; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a copy of the registry card from the commercial register; </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 14.11.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.02.2002 - RT I 2001, 93, 565) </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 14.11.2001 entered into force 01.02.2002 - RT I 2001, 93, 565) </inglise>
<eesti>3) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse &otilde;iend maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a statement from the local Tax Board Office certifying the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>4) eelmise majandusaasta kinnitatud aruanne; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the approved annual report for the previous year; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kaupade ja teenuste loetelu, mille m&uuml;&uuml;ki, eksporti v&otilde;i importi loa taotleja kavandab v&otilde;i teostab, ja eelmise majandusaasta k&auml;ive; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a list of goods and services which the applicant for a licence intends to sell, export or import or which the applicant sells, exports or imports, and turn-over of the previous financial year; </inglise>
<eesti>6) v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja tegevuspiirkonna skemaatiline plaan ja kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a schematic plan and a description of the licensed territory of the network operator; </inglise>
<eesti>7) Tolliameti &otilde;iend maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta, kui tegevusluba taotletakse impordiks; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a certificate from the Customs Board confirming the absence of tax arrears if the activity licence is applied for to engage in import; </inglise>
<eesti>8) taotleja kirjalik t&otilde;endus, et tal on tehnilised v&otilde;imalused ja vajaliku oskusega personal tegutsemiseks taotluses m&auml;rgitud tegevusalal ning et tema tegevus vastab keskkonnakaitse, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja muudele &otilde;igusaktidega etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>8) written confirmation from the applicant that the applicant has the technical capability and personnel with the necessary skills to operate in the area of activity indicated in the application and that the applicant's activities comply with the environmental protection and occupational safety requirements and other requirements prescribed by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Asutamisel olevale &auml;ri&uuml;hingule antakse turuluba kuni kaheks aastaks ja taotlusele lisatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A company which is being founded shall be issued a market licence for up to two years and the following shall be appended to the application: </inglise>
<eesti>1) asutamislepingu, asutamisotsuse v&otilde;i &uuml;hingulepingu kinnitatud koopia koopia; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a certified copy of the memorandum of association, foundation resolution or partnership agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>(14.11.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.02.2002 - RT I 2001, 93, 565) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.11.2001 entered into force 01.02.2002 - RT I 2001, 93, 565) </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 14.11.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.02.2002 - RT I 2001, 93, 565) </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 14.11.2001 entered into force 01.02.2002 - RT I 2001, 93, 565) </inglise>
<eesti>3) kaupade ja teenuste loetelu, mille m&uuml;&uuml;ki, eksporti v&otilde;i importi loa taotleja kavandab; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a list of goods and services which the applicant for a licence intends to sell, export or import; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja tegevuspiirkonna skemaatiline plaan ja kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a schematic plan and a description of the licensed territory of the network operator; </inglise>
<eesti>5) taotleja kirjalik t&otilde;endus, et tal on tehnilised v&otilde;imalused ja vajaliku oskusega personal tegutsemiseks taotluses m&auml;rgitud tegevusalal ning et tema tegevus vastab keskkonnakaitse, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja muudele &otilde;igusaktidega etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>5) written confirmation from the applicant that the applicant has the technical capability and personnel with the necessary skills to operate in the area of activity indicated in the application and that the applicant's activities comply with the environmental protection and occupational safety requirements and other requirements prescribed by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Turuloa taotlemisel esitatud dokumente taotlejale ei tagastata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Documents provided upon application for a market licence shall not be returned to the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vedelk&uuml;tuse (v&auml;lja arvatud vedelgaas) impordiks v&otilde;ib turuluba taotleda ja omada ettev&otilde;tja, kelle osa- v&otilde;i aktsiakapital on v&auml;hemalt 10 miljonit krooni ja kes kohustub hoidma vedelk&uuml;tuse miinimumvaru, kui selline kohustus on seadusega ette n&auml;htud. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A market licence for the import of liquid fuel (except liquefied gas) may be applied for and held by an undertaking whose share capital is at least ten million kroons and who undertakes to store minimum stocks of liquid fuel if such obligation is prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Vedelk&uuml;tuse (v&auml;lja arvatud vedelgaas) m&uuml;&uuml;giks v&otilde;ib turuluba taotleda ja omada ettev&otilde;tja, kelle osa- v&otilde;i aktsiakapital on v&auml;hemalt 2 miljonit krooni v&otilde;i kellel on vastutuskindlustuse leping kindlustussumma alamm&auml;&auml;raga v&auml;hemalt 1 miljon krooni, mis tagab k&uuml;tuseettev&otilde;tja poolt m&uuml;&uuml;dud kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele mittevastava k&uuml;tusega tekitatud varalise kahju h&uuml;vitamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A market licence for the sale of liquid fuel (except liquefied gas) may be applied for and held by an undertaking whose share capital is at least two million kroons or who has entered into a liability insurance contract with the minimum amount of insurance coverage of at least one million kroons to ensure compensation for proprietary damage caused by fuel not in compliance with the quality requirements which is sold by the fuel undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Vedelk&uuml;tuse impordiks v&otilde;ib turuluba taotleda &auml;riregistrisse kantud &auml;ri&uuml;hing, kes on tegelenud vedelk&uuml;tuse m&uuml;&uuml;giga Eestis v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A market licence for the import of liquid fuel may be applied for by a company entered in the commercial register which has been engaged in the sale of liquid fuel in Estonia for at least two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Turuloa andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Issue of market licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Energiaturu Inspektsioon teeb 60 p&auml;eva jooksul, alates k&auml;esoleva seaduse n&otilde;uetele vastava taotluse ja k&otilde;igi taotluse juurde kuuluvate dokumentide saamisest, turuloa andmise v&otilde;i turuloa andmisest keeldumise otsuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Energy Market Inspectorate shall make a decision to issue a market licence or to refuse to issue a market licence within sixty days as of the receipt of an application which complies with the requirements specified in this Act and of all documents appended thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse korral, mis on esitatud tegevuse alustamiseks ja &auml;riregistrisse kandmiseks, teeb Energiaturu Inspektsioon turuloa andmise v&otilde;i turuloa andmisest keeldumise otsuse 30 p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of an application which is submitted to commence activities and to be entered in the commercial register, the Energy Market Inspectorate shall make a decision to issue a market licence or to refuse to issue a market licence within thirty days. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turuloa andmise k&uuml;simuse otsustamiseks v&otilde;ib Energiaturu Inspektsiooni p&auml;dev ametiisik k&uuml;sida taotlemisel esitatud andmete kohta taotlejalt v&otilde;i tema esindajalt, samuti riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutuselt t&auml;psustavaid lisaandmeid ja kontrollida esitatud andmete &otilde;igsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to decide the matter of issuing a market licence, a competent official of the Energy Market Inspectorate may ask the applicant or a representative of the applicant and state or local government agencies for more specific additional information concerning the information submitted upon application and verify the correctness of information submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Energia- v&otilde;i v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjale antakse turuluba tingimusel, et ta on riigiga s&otilde;lminud lepingu, millega tagatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 l&otilde;ikes 1, &sect; 14 l&otilde;igetes 3 ja 4 ning &sect; 15 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine ka juhul, kui turuluba tunnistatakse kehtetuks v&otilde;i kui selle kehtivus l&otilde;peb. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A market licence is issued to an energy undertaking or network operator on the condition that the energy undertaking or network operator has entered into a contract with the state to ensure performance of the obligations specified in subsections 11 (1), 14 (3), 14 (4) and 15 (1) of this Act even if a market licence is revoked or expires. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepinguga v&otilde;ib muu hulgas n&auml;ha ette energia- v&otilde;i v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tte majandamiseks vajaliku vara v&otilde;&otilde;randamise riigile v&otilde;i energia- v&otilde;i v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja aktsiate v&otilde;i osade t&auml;ieliku v&otilde;i osalise v&otilde;&otilde;randamise riigile koos vastava h&uuml;vitise maksmisega, et tagada energia- v&otilde;i v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine. </eesti>
<inglise>Among other matters, such contract may prescribe the transfer of assets necessary for the management of the energy or network enterprise to the state, or the whole or partial transfer to the state of the shares of the energy undertaking or network operator together with payment of appropriate compensation, to ensure performance of the obligations of the energy undertaking or network operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kuni k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud viisil riigi poolt energia- v&otilde;i v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tte &uuml;le kontrolli v&otilde;tmiseni v&otilde;i muude lepingus etten&auml;htud abin&otilde;ude rakendamiseni on energia- v&otilde;i v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja kohustatud j&auml;tkama oma tegevust, et tagada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine. (5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud leping j&otilde;ustub turuloa andmisest ja riigi nimel kirjutab lepingule alla Energiaturu Inspektsiooni peadirektor. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Until the state obtains control of an energy or network enterprise pursuant to subsection (3) of this section or exercises other contractual remedies, the energy undertaking or network operator is required to continue its activities to ensure performance of the obligations provided for in subsection (3) of this section. (5) The contract specified in subsection (3) of this section shall be binding as of the issue of a market licence, and on behalf of the state, the contract shall be signed by the Director General of the Energy Market Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9 (3). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Turuloale kantavad andmed </eesti>
<inglise>Information to be entered on market licence </inglise>
<eesti>Turuloale kantakse j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>The following information shall be entered on a market licence: </inglise>
<eesti>1) turuloa number; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the number of the market licence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) turuloa andmise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date of issue of the market licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettev&otilde;tja &auml;rinimi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the business name of the undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>4) registrikood; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the registry code; </inglise>
<eesti>5) asukoha aadress ja muud kontaktandmed; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the address of the seat and other details; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tegevusalad, millel tegutsemiseks on turuluba antud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) areas of activity for which the market licence is issued; </inglise>
<eesti>7) tegevuspiirkond; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the licensed territory; </inglise>
<eesti>8) turuloa andja ametiisiku allkiri, nimi ja ametinimetus. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the signature, name and official title of an official of the issuer of the market licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9 (4). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9 (4). </inglise>
<eesti>Turuloa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to issue market licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuloa andmisest keeldutakse, kui turuluba taotlev ettev&otilde;tja ei esita n&otilde;uetekohaseid dokumente v&otilde;i esitab eksitavaid, tegelikkusele mittevastavaid andmeid v&otilde;i v&otilde;ltsitud dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The issue of a market licence shall be refused if the undertaking applying for the market licence fails to submit documents in compliance with the requirements or submits misleading or inaccurate information or falsified documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettev&otilde;tjale, kelle turuluba on tunnistatud kehtetuks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 (5) alusel, ei anta uut turuluba kolme aasta jooksul loa kehtetuks tunnistamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An undertaking whose market licence is revoked on the basis of &sect; 9 (5) of this Act shall not be issued a new market licence during three years as of the date of revocation of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turuloa andmisest v&otilde;ib keelduda, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The issue of a market licence may be refused if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Energiaturu Inspektsioonil on p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlus taotleja v&otilde;imes t&auml;ita k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 6 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid, </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Energy Market Inspectorate has reason to doubt the applicant's capability to meet the requirements provided for in subsection 9 (6) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Energiaturu Inspektsioonil on p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlus taotleja majandusliku seisundi usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsuses v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>2) the Energy Market Inspectorate has reason to doubt the reliability of the financial status of the applicant, or </inglise>
<eesti>3) keeldumine l&auml;htub riigi majanduspoliitilistest huvidest, mis tuginevad Riigikogu v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse otsustele. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the refusal derives from national economic policy interests which are based on the resolutions of the Riigikogu (2) or the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Turuloa andmisest keeldumisest teavitatakse taotlejat kirjalikult kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul vastava otsuse tegemisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An applicant shall be notified of a refusal to issue a market licence in writing within three working days as of the date on which the corresponding decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turuloa andmisest keeldumine ei v&otilde;ta taotlejalt &otilde;igust taotleda uuesti turuluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A refusal to issue a market licence does not deprive the applicant of the right to apply for a market licence again. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9 (5). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9 (5). </inglise>
<eesti>Turuloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of market licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse ja ettev&otilde;tja turuloa tingimuste t&auml;itmise &uuml;le teostab j&auml;relevalvet ja vajaduse korral tunnistab turuloa kehtetuks Energiaturu Inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supervision over compliance with this Act and the conditions of the market licence of an undertaking is exercised by the Energy Market Inspectorate and, if necessary, the Energy Market Inspectorate revokes the market licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Energiaturu Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus tunnistada turuluba kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Energy Market Inspectorate has the right to revoke a market licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loa omanik on rikkunud k&auml;esolevat seadust v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusakti; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the holder of the licence violates this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksuhalduri teatel on loa omanik korduvalt rikkunud maksuseadusi v&otilde;i tolliseaduse &sect; 65 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud tollieeskirju; </eesti>
<inglise>2) according to tax authorities, the holder of the licence has repeatedly violated tax laws or the customs rules specified in clauses 65 (1) 2) and 3) of the Customs Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) loa omanik ei ole loas m&auml;rgitud tegevusalal alustanud tegevust 12 kuu jooksul loas s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajast arvates; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the holder of the licence fails to commence activities in the area of activity specified in the licence within twelve months after the term specified in the licence; </inglise>
<eesti>4) loa omanik seda taotleb. </eesti>
<inglise>4) so requested by the holder of the licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettev&otilde;tja l&otilde;petamisel kaotab temale antud turuluba kehtivuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an undertaking terminates its activities, the market licence issued thereto becomes invalid. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Energia s&auml;&auml;stmine ja keskkonnakaitse </eesti>
<inglise>Energy conservation and environmental protection </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tjad on kohustatud soodustama tarbijate tegevust k&uuml;tuse ja energia s&auml;&auml;stmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Fuel and energy enterprises are required to promote conservation of fuel and energy by users. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&uuml;tuse ja energia tootmine, edastamine, muundamine ja jaotamine tuleb korraldada nii, et sellest tulenevad keskkonnakahjustused ei &uuml;letaks rahvusvaheliste lepingute ja keskkonnaalaste &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud piire. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The production, transport or transmission, conversion and distribution of fuel and energy shall be organised such that environmental damage arising therefrom does not exceed the limits established by international agreements and environmental legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Energiakasutuse efektiivsuse t&otilde;stmiseks, keskkonna kvaliteedi s&auml;ilitamiseks ja looduslike ressursside ratsionaalseks kasutamiseks kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus energias&auml;&auml;stu sihtprogrammi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to increase energy efficiency, preserve the quality of the environment and to use natural resources rationally, the Government of the Republic shall approve an energy conservation programme. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Tarbijate varustamine energia, vedelk&uuml;tuse ja v&otilde;rgugaasiga </eesti>
<inglise>Supply of energy, liquid fuel and network gas to users </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tarbijate varustamine energia, vedelk&uuml;tuse ja v&otilde;rgugaasiga peab olema pidev, kui ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Users shall have an uninterrupted supply of energy, liquid fuel and network gas, unless otherwise agreed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tja tegevus- ja arenduskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Activity and development obligations of fuel and energy undertakings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tjale, kelle tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada tarbijate k&uuml;tuse v&otilde;i energiaga varustamise v&auml;henemise v&otilde;i katkemise v&otilde;i v&auml;hendab Eesti elektris&uuml;steemi t&ouml;&ouml;kindlust, paneb Energiaturu Inspektsioon tegevus- ja arenduskohustuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Energy Market Inspectorate shall impose activity and development obligations on fuel and energy undertakings whose activity or failure to act could cause a reduction or interruption of the fuel or energy supply to users, or decrease the reliability of Estonia's power system. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevus- ja arenduskohustus on k&auml;esolevas seaduses turuloaga kaasnev lisatingimus, mis vormistatakse lepingu kujul Energiaturu Inspektsiooni ja turuluba omava v&otilde;i taotleva ettev&otilde;tja vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In this Act, activity and development obligations are supplementary conditions of a market licence, which are formalised in a contract between the Energy Market Inspectorate and the market licensee or undertaking applying for a market licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettev&otilde;tja kohustub oma tegevuspiirkonnas paiknevate k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaseadmete ning k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaehitiste tootmisv&otilde;imsust v&otilde;i varustuskindlust s&auml;ilitama v&otilde;i muutma lepingus etten&auml;htud m&auml;&auml;ral ning t&auml;htaegadel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Undertakings shall maintain or alter the production capacity or reliability of fuel and energy equipment and constructions within their licensed territory, to the extent and within the time period prescribed in the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Energiaturu Inspektsioon arvestab ettev&otilde;tja poolt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud lepingu t&auml;itmiseks tehtud &otilde;igustatud ja p&otilde;hjendatud kulutusi toodangu hinna ja m&uuml;&uuml;gitingimuste koosk&otilde;lastamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In approving product prices and conditions of sale, the Energy Market Inspectorate shall take into account the legitimate and substantiated expenses incurred by the undertaking in order to comply with the contract specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;tuse- ja energiamajanduse arengukava </eesti>
<inglise>Development plan for fuel and energy sector </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&uuml;tuse- ja energiamajanduse pikaajalise riikliku arengukava esitab Vabariigi Valitsus olulise t&auml;htsusega riigielu k&uuml;simusena Riigikogule kinnitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Government of the Republic shall submit a long-term national development plan for the fuel and energy sector to the Riigikogu for approval as an essential national issue. </inglise>
<eesti>Arengukavas peab ette n&auml;gema ka Eesti elektris&uuml;steemi t&ouml;&ouml; s&uuml;nkroniseerimise ja koost&ouml;&ouml; Euroopa Liidu liikmesriikide elektris&uuml;steemidega. </eesti>
<inglise>The development plan shall provide for the synchronisation and co-operation of the Estonian power system with the power systems of the Member States of the European Union. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turuluba omavad k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tjad on kohustatud esitama Majandusministeeriumile tema taotlusel pikaajalise riikliku arengukava koostamiseks vajalikke andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Fuel and energy undertakings who hold market licences are required upon request to submit information to the Ministry of Economic Affairs which is necessary for preparation of a long-term national development plan. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Network operators </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses kasutatakse m&otilde;istet v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja, m&auml;&auml;ratlemaks ettev&otilde;tjat, kelle omandis v&otilde;i valduses on elektriliin v&otilde;i -v&otilde;rk, soojustorustik v&otilde;i -v&otilde;rk, gaasitorustik v&otilde;i -v&otilde;rk, vedelk&uuml;tuse torustik v&otilde;i -v&otilde;rk ning mille kaudu edastatakse v&otilde;i jaotatakse elektrit, soojust, v&otilde;rgugaasi v&otilde;i vedelk&uuml;tust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In this Act, "network operator" means an undertakingr which owns or possesses a power line or network, a heat pipeline or network, a gas pipeline or network, or a liquid fuel pipeline or network through which electric power, heat, network gas or liquid fuel is transmitted, transported or distributed. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) V&otilde;rguks k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses ei loeta ehitisse paigaldatud omavahel &uuml;hendatud seadmeid, elektriliine v&otilde;i torustikku (ja nendega &uuml;hendatud seadmeid), mille kaudu jaotatakse energiat v&otilde;i v&otilde;rgugaasi &uuml;he kinnisasja v&otilde;i vallasasjaks oleva ehitise ja selle teenindamiseks vajaliku maa piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) For the purposes of this Act, inter-connected equipment, power lines or pipelines installed in a structure (and equipment connected thereto) through which energy or network gas is distributed within the structure which is an immovable or a movable and land necessary for servicing the structure are not deemed to be a network. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja tegevuspiirkond on turuloaga m&auml;&auml;ratud piirkond, kus asuvad tema omandis v&otilde;i valduses olevad energia-, gaasi- v&otilde;i vedelk&uuml;tusev&otilde;rgud, v&otilde;i piirkond, mille suhtes ettev&otilde;tjale on pandud tegevus- ja arenduskohustus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The licensed territory of a network operator is an area specified by the market licence where the energy, gas or liquid fuel networks owned or possessed by the undertaking are located, or an area in respect of which the undertaking has activity and development obligations. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjal v&otilde;ib olla mitu tegevuspiirkonda. </eesti>
<inglise>A network operator may have several licensed territories. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja vastutab tema omandis v&otilde;i valduses oleva v&otilde;rgu toimimise, korrasoleku ja arendamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Network operators are responsible for the functioning, maintenance and development of the networks which they own or possess. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja peab arendama tema omandis v&otilde;i valduses olevat energia-, vedelk&uuml;tuse- ja gaasiv&otilde;rku selliselt, et oleks tagatud k&otilde;igi v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja tegevuspiirkonnas olevate tarbijate ja energiaettev&otilde;tjate v&otilde;rku &uuml;hendamine vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 16 ning energia, vedelk&uuml;tuse v&otilde;i v&otilde;rgugaasiga varustamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Network operators shall develop the energy, liquid fuel and gas networks which they own or possess such that connection to the networks pursuant to &sect; 16 of this Act and the supply of energy, liquid fuel or network gas are guaranteed to all users and energy undertakings in the network operator's licensed territory. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Energia-, vedelk&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i gaasiv&otilde;rguga &uuml;hendatud seadmed ja v&otilde;rgud ei tohi h&auml;irida teisi v&otilde;rke ja tarbijaid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Equipment and networks connected to energy, liquid fuel or gas networks shall not disturb other networks or users. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja &otilde;igused, kohustused ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Rights, obligations and liabilities of network operators </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud tagama tema omandis v&otilde;i valduses oleva v&otilde;rguga &uuml;hendatud tarbijate varustamise, m&uuml;&uuml;es tarbijale energiat, vedelk&uuml;tust v&otilde;i v&otilde;rgugaasi v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;es energia, vedelk&uuml;tuse v&otilde;i v&otilde;rgugaasi edastamise v&otilde;i jaotamise teenust, kui tarbija ostab energiat, vedelk&uuml;tust v&otilde;i v&otilde;rgugaasi teiselt m&uuml;&uuml;jalt, kellelt ostmine on majanduslikult p&otilde;hjendatud ja tehniliselt v&otilde;imalik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Network operators are required to ensure supply to users who are connected to the network which they own or possess, by selling energy, liquid fuel or network gas, or by selling services for the transmission, transport or distribution of energy, liquid fuel or network gas to users who purchase energy, liquid fuel or network gas from other sellers from whom such purchase is economically justified and technically possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjal on oma tegevuspiirkonnas vastava v&otilde;rguliigi arendamise kohustus vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 12. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Network operators are required to develop energy networks within their licensed territories in accordance with &sect; 12 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevas seaduses loetakse v&otilde;rguteenuseks edastamis- ja jaotamisteenuse osutamist v&otilde;rgu&uuml;henduse kaudu ning sellise &uuml;henduse olemasolu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For the purposes of this Act, "network service" means the provision of transmission or transport and distribution services using a network connection and the existence of such connection. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjal on kohustus tehniliste v&otilde;imaluste piires osutada edastamis- v&otilde;i jaotamisteenust k&otilde;igile teistele v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjatele ja suurtarbijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>Insofar as technically possible, network operators are required to provide transmission, transport or distribution services to all other network operators and large users. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja peab v&otilde;rguteenuste tariifid enne kehtestamist koosk&otilde;lastama Energiaturu Inspektsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Network operators are required to obtain the approval of the Energy Market Inspectorate to the rates for network services prior to the establishment thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rguteenuste tariifide kujundamisel peab v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja j&auml;rgima k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;igetes 4 ja 5 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>Network operators are required to observe the provisions of subsections 19 (4) and (5) of this Act upon the formation of the rates for network services. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Uuml;hes v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja tegevuspiirkonnas ei tohi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud edastamis- v&otilde;i jaotamisteenuste tariifid s&otilde;ltuda edastamise v&otilde;i jaotamise kaugusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Within the licensed territory of one network operator, the transmission, transport or distribution rates set out in subsection (4) of this section shall not be dependent on the distance of transmission, transport or distribution. </inglise>
<eesti>Edastamis- v&otilde;i jaotamistasu v&otilde;ib s&otilde;ltuda edastatava v&otilde;i jaotatava k&uuml;tuse ja energia kogusest, v&otilde;imsusgraafikust, s&uuml;steemi tippkoormuse tundidest, pingetasemest ja energiavarustuse kindlusest. </eesti>
<inglise>Transmission, transport or distribution rates may depend on the amount of fuel and energy to be transported, transmitted or distributed, voltage schedules, system-wide peak hours, voltage levels and the reliability of energy supplied. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Jaotusv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjal on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 28 (1) nimetatud alternatiivselt toodetud elektrienergia ostukohustuse suurusest s&otilde;ltuvalt taotleda Energiaturu Inspektsioonilt p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja poolt rakendatava edastamistariifi v&auml;hendamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Depending on the extent of the obligation to purchase alternatively produced energy specified in &sect; 28 (1) of this Act, a distribution network operator has the right to apply to the Energy Market Inspectorate for a reduction in the transmission or transport rate applied by a transmission network operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) P&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja peab oma tegevuspiirkonnas kehtivaid edastamistariife diferentseerima Energiaturu Inspektsiooni ettekirjutuse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A transmission network operator shall differentiate the transmission and transport rates valid in the operator's licensed territory pursuant to a precept of the Energy Market Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Elektri-, gaasi- ja kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndid ning nendega seotud kitsendused </eesti>
<inglise>Protection zones for power, gas and district heating networks and restrictions related thereto </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektri-, gaasi- ja kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;nd on neid tehnov&otilde;rke (elektriliinid, gaasi- ja kaugk&uuml;ttetorustikud ning nendega liituvad ehitised) &uuml;mbritsev maa-ala, &otilde;huruum v&otilde;i veekogu, kus tehnov&otilde;rkude ohust ja nende kaitse vajadusest tulenevalt kitsendatakse kinnisasja omaniku v&otilde;i valdaja tegevust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A protection zone for a power, gas or district heating network is the land, air space or body of water surrounding such utility network (power lines, gas and district heating pipe systems and structures connected therewith), where the activities of the owner or possessor of an immovable are restricted due to the danger posed by the utility network and the necessity for its protection. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektri-, gaasi- ja kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi ulatus (m&otilde;&otilde;tmed) tulenevalt nende tehnov&otilde;rkude ohutasemest, pingest, survest, v&otilde;imsusest ja asukohast kehtestatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The size (dimensions) of a protection zone for a power, gas or district heating network is established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic based on the danger level, voltage, pressure, capacity and location of the utility network. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elektri-, gaasi- ja kaugk&uuml;tte kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis peab kinnisasja omanik v&otilde;i valdaja kinni pidama j&auml;rgmistest kitsendustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Within a protection zone for a power, gas or district heating network, the owner or possessor of an immovable shall observe the following restrictions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) elektriv&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on keelatud t&otilde;kestada juurdep&auml;&auml;su elektriv&otilde;rgu ehitisteni, ladustada j&auml;&auml;tmeid, tuleohtlikke materjale ja aineid, teha tuld, p&otilde;hjustada oma tegevusega elektriv&otilde;rgu ehitiste saastamist ja korrosiooni, korraldada &uuml;le 1000 V pingega elektriv&otilde;rgu &otilde;huliinide kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis massi&uuml;ritusi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) within a power network protection zone, it is prohibited to prevent access to power network structures, store waste, flammable materials and substances, ignite open flames, cause the contamination or corrosion of power network constructions, or organise public events in a power network protection zone for overhead power lines with a voltage of over 1000 V; </inglise>
<eesti>2) elektriv&otilde;rgu veekaabelliinide kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on keelatud teha s&uuml;vendust&ouml;id, vees&otilde;idukiga ankrusse heita, liikuda heidetud ankru, kettide, logide, traalide ja v&otilde;rkudega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) within a power network protection zone for submerged cable lines, it is prohibited to perform dredging operations, moor water craft, or move with dropped anchor, chains, logs, trawls or nets; </inglise>
<eesti>3) gaasiv&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on keelatud rajada alalisi ehitisi, teha tuld, l&auml;bi viia l&otilde;hket&ouml;id, ladustada kemikaale, j&auml;&auml;tmeid v&otilde;i v&auml;etisi, rajada uitvoole tekitavaid elektris&uuml;steeme, kuni 16 bar t&ouml;&ouml;survega gaasiv&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis ning &uuml;le 16 bar t&ouml;&ouml;survega gaasiv&otilde;rgu hooldusribas (6 m maariba piki torustiku telge) istutada puid ja p&otilde;&otilde;said, parkida mehhanisme ja masinaid ning ladustada materjale; </eesti>
<inglise>3) within a gas network protection zone, it is prohibited to construct permanent structures, ignite open flames, perform blasting operations, store chemicals, waste or fertilizers, or construct power systems which cause earth currents; within a gas network protection zone of an operating pressure of up to 16 bar, and within a gas network maintenance zone (a 6 m long strip of earth along the piping axis) of an operating pressure of over 16 bar, it is prohibited to plant trees and shrubs, park equipment and vehicles, or store materials; </inglise>
<eesti>4) veekogus asuva gaasiv&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on keelatud teha s&uuml;vendust&ouml;id, vees&otilde;idukiga ankrusse heita, liikuda heidetud ankru, kettide, logide, traalide ja v&otilde;rkudega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) within a gas network protection zone located in a body of water, it is prohibited to perform dredging operations, moor water craft, or move with dropped anchor, chains, logs, trawls or nets; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on keelatud t&otilde;kestada juurdep&auml;&auml;su kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgule, rajada alalisi ehitisi, ladustada j&auml;&auml;tmeid, kemikaale v&otilde;i v&auml;etisi, istutada puid ja p&otilde;&otilde;said ning teha muid tegevusi, mis v&otilde;ivad kahjustada kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgu konstruktsioone; </eesti>
<inglise>5) within a district heating network protection zone, it is prohibited to prevent access to the district heating network, construct permanent structures, store waste, chemicals or fertilizers, plant trees and shrubs, or perform other activities which may damage the district heating network constructions; </inglise>
<eesti>6) elektriv&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on ilma v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja loata keelatud ehitada, rekonstrueerida v&otilde;i lammutada hooneid ja rajatisi, teha mis tahes m&auml;e-, laadimis-, s&uuml;vendus-, l&otilde;hkamis-, &uuml;leujutus-, niisutus- ja maaparandust&ouml;id, istutada ja langetada puid ja p&otilde;&otilde;said; </eesti>
<inglise>6) within a power network protection zone, it is prohibited, without the permission of the network operator, to build, reconstruct or demolish buildings and constructions, perform any excavation, loading, dredging, blasting, flooding, irrigation and land improvement operations, or plant or remove trees or shrubs; </inglise>
<eesti>7) elektriv&otilde;rgu &otilde;huliinide kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on ilma v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja loata keelatud s&otilde;ita masinate ja mehhanismidega, mille &uuml;ldk&otilde;rgus maapinnast koos veosega v&otilde;i ilma on &uuml;le 4,5 m; &uuml;le 1000 V pingega elektriv&otilde;rgu &otilde;huliinide kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis rajada karjaaedu, traattarasid ja loomade joogikohti; </eesti>
<inglise>7) within a power network protection zone for overhead transmission lines, it is prohibited, without the permission of the network operator, to drive vehicles and equipment whose height above ground level, with or without cargo, exceeds 4.5 m; within a power network protection zone for overhead transmission lines of a voltage of over 1000 V, it is prohibited to construct stock yards, wire fences and watering places for livestock; </inglise>
<eesti>8) elektriv&otilde;rgu maakaabelliinide kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on ilma v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja loata keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;tada l&ouml;&ouml;kmehhanismidega, planeerida pinnast, teha mullat&ouml;id s&uuml;gavamal kui 0,3 m, k&uuml;ntaval maal s&uuml;gavamal kui 0,45 m ning ladustada ja teisaldada raskusi; </eesti>
<inglise>8) within a power network protection zone for underground cable lines, it is prohibited, without the permission of the network operator, to operate impact mechanisms, level ground, perform earthwork at a depth exceeding 0.3 m or 0.45 m in land to be ploughed, or to store or handle loads; </inglise>
<eesti>9) elektriv&otilde;rgu veekaabelliinide kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on ilma v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja loata keelatud paigaldada vees&otilde;idukite liiklust&auml;hiseid ja poisid ning l&otilde;hata ja varuda j&auml;&auml;d; </eesti>
<inglise>9) within a power network protection zone for submerged cable lines, it is prohibited, without the permission of the network operator, to locate traffic signs and buoys for water craft, or to blast or store ice; </inglise>
<eesti>10) gaasiv&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on keelatud ilma v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja loata teha puurimis- ja kaevamist&ouml;id, p&uuml;stitada ajutisi ehitisi ning teha metsaraiet ja metsaveo&uuml;les&otilde;ite; </eesti>
<inglise>10) within a gas network protection zone, it is prohibited, without the permission of the network operator, to perform boring or excavation operations, construct temporary structures, perform logging or make logging crossings; </inglise>
<eesti>11) kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgu kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on keelatud ilma v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja loata teha l&otilde;hkamis-, puurimis- ja kaevet&ouml;id, samuti &uuml;leujutus-, niisutus- ja maaparandust&ouml;id, paigaldada t&auml;iendavaid kommunikatsioone, teha ehitust&ouml;id, p&uuml;stitada ajutisi ehitisi, rajada parkimisplatse, ladustada ja teisaldada materjale, organiseerida &uuml;les&otilde;ite, paigaldada kinnisasja omaniku v&otilde;i valdaja ehitust l&auml;bivates kaugk&uuml;ttev&otilde;rgu tehnilistes koridorides t&auml;iendavaid kommunikatsioone ja teha &uuml;mberehitusi. </eesti>
<inglise>11) within a district heating network protection zone, it is prohibited, without the permission of the network operator, to perform blasting, boring or excavation operations as well as flooding, irrigation or land improvement operations, to locate supplementary communications lines, perform construction work, construct temporary structures, construct car parks, store or handle materials, organise crossings, locate supplementary communications lines or perform reconstruction work in the technical corridors of a district heating network which run through a structure belonging to the owner or possessor of an immovable. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Energia- v&otilde;i gaasiv&otilde;rguga liitumine </eesti>
<inglise>Connection to energy or gas networks </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja peab v&otilde;imaldama tema omandis v&otilde;i valduses oleva v&otilde;rguga liitumise (sealhulgas v&otilde;rgu&uuml;henduse kasutamise) k&otilde;igile tema tegevuspiirkonnas asuvaile ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja teiste &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele vastavatele tarbijatele, tootjatele ning energia- v&otilde;i gaasiv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A network operator shall allow connection to a network owned or possessed by the network operator (including the use of a network connection) to all users, producers and energy or gas network operators that are within the network operator's licensed territory and comply with requirements established by this Act and other legislation </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjal on &otilde;igus v&otilde;tta v&otilde;rguga liitujatelt p&otilde;hjendatud liitumistasu, mis on arvestatud vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud korrale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Network operators have the right to collect, from connected parties, justified connection charges calculated pursuant to the procedure specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elektriv&otilde;rguga liitumise ja liitumistasu arvestamise korra, soojusv&otilde;rguga liitumise ja liitumistasu arvestamise korra ning gaasiv&otilde;rguga liitumise ja liitumistasu arvestamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for connection to a power network and the calculation of connection charges, the procedure for connection to a heat network and the calculation of connection charges and the procedure for connection to a gas network and the calculation of connection charges shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;tuse- ja energiamajandus </eesti>
<inglise>Fuel and Energy Sector </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Energia ja k&uuml;tuse m&uuml;&uuml;k ning v&otilde;rguteenuse osutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Sale of fuel and energy and provision of network services </inglise>
<eesti>Energiat ja k&uuml;tust m&uuml;&uuml;akse ning v&otilde;rguteenust osutatakse lepingu alusel, milles m&auml;&auml;ratakse m&uuml;&uuml;dava k&uuml;tuse ja energia kogus, kvaliteet, varustamiskindlus, hind v&otilde;i hinna m&auml;&auml;ramise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted, poolte kohustused, vastutus ning muud lepingutingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>Energy or fuel is sold and network services are provided on the basis of a contract which determines the amount, quality, reliability of supply, price or principles of pricing of the fuel or energy to be sold or network services to be provided, the obligations of the parties, liabilities and other contractual terms. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Energia v&otilde;i gaasi m&uuml;&uuml;k v&otilde;rgu kaudu </eesti>
<inglise>Sale of energy or gas through networks </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Suurtarbijad k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In this Act, large users are defined as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) elektri- ja soojusenergia suurtarbija m&auml;&auml;ratluse kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus, l&auml;htudes tema tarbimisv&otilde;imsusest ja tema poolt aastas oma tarbeks tarbitava energia kogusest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the definition of "large user of electrical power and heat" shall be established by the Government of the Republic based on the usage capacity of the user and the amount of energy used by the user per year; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>3) gaasi suurtarbija on tarbija, kes kasutab gaasi t&ouml;&ouml;stuses v&otilde;i kaugk&uuml;tte katlamajas; </eesti>
<inglise>3) "large user of gas" means a user who uses gas in industry or in a district heating power station; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vedelk&uuml;tuse suurtarbija on k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses iga vedelk&uuml;tuse v&otilde;rgust tarbija. </eesti>
<inglise>4) for the purpose of this Act, "large user of liquid fuel" means any user of liquid fuel from a network. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 3 loetlemata tarbijad on v&auml;iketarbijad. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Users who are not specified in clauses (1) 1) and 3) of this section are small users. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&otilde;rguga &uuml;hendatud suurtarbijal on &otilde;igus osta energiat v&otilde;i gaasi v&otilde;rgu tehniliste v&otilde;imaluste piires igalt Eesti Vabariigi territooriumil tegutsevalt energia- v&otilde;i v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Large users who are connected to a network have the right, within the limits of the network's technical possibilities, to purchase energy or gas from any energy or network operator operating within the territory of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;iketarbijad ostavad energiat v&otilde;i v&otilde;rgugaasi neid teenindavalt v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjalt v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 6 nimetatud energia tootjalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Small users shall purchase energy or network gas from the network operator who services them or from an energy producer specified in subsection (6) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu ettepanekul v&otilde;ib v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja tegevuspiirkonnas moodustada mitu m&uuml;&uuml;gipiirkonda. </eesti>
<inglise>On the proposal of the local government council, a network operator may form several sales territories within a licensed territory. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hes m&uuml;&uuml;gipiirkonnas kehtestatakse samasse tarbijagruppi kuuluvatele tarbijatele &uuml;htsed tariifid. </eesti>
<inglise>The same tariffs are established throughout one sales territory for users belonging to the same user group. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Energia tootjal on &otilde;igus m&uuml;&uuml;a energiat v&otilde;rgu tehniliste v&otilde;imaluste piires igale Eesti Vabariigi territooriumil paiknevale suurtarbijale ning v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjale, kui viimane kasutab seda edasim&uuml;&uuml;giks oma v&otilde;rguga &uuml;hendatud suurtarbijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Within the limits of the technical possibilities of the network, energy producers have the right to sell energy to every large user and network operator within the territory of the Republic of Estonia if the large user or network operator resells the energy to other large users connected to the network of the large user or network operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui energia tootja installeeritud energiaseadmete elektriline v&otilde;imsus energia tootja kohta ei &uuml;leta 10 MW ning kui elektrienergia tootmine toimub soojuse ja elektrienergia koostootmise protsessis v&otilde;i alternatiivselt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 (1) t&auml;henduses, on tal &otilde;igus igale tarbijale selle tarbijaga s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel m&uuml;&uuml;a elektrienergiat vahetult v&otilde;i v&otilde;rgu tehniliste v&otilde;imaluste piires v&otilde;rgu kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If the electric capacity of energy equipment installed by an energy producer does not exceed 10 MW per energy producer and if electric power is produced in the process of combined heat and power production or alternatively within the meaning of &sect; 28 (1) of this Act, the energy producer has the right to sell electric power directly or, within the limits of the network's technical possibilities, through a network to every user on the basis of a contract entered into with the user. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Energiaettev&otilde;tjad ja suurtarbijad on kohustatud tagama, et nende energiatoodang ja -hanked v&otilde;rduksid nende energiam&uuml;&uuml;gi ja -tarbimisega igal ajahetkel. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Energy undertakings and large users must ensure that their energy production and procurement equal their energy sales and consumption at all times. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Turgu valitsev k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Fuel or energy undertakings dominating the market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turgu valitseva k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja m&auml;&auml;ratlus vastab konkurentsiseaduse (RT I 1998, 30, 410) paragrahv 13 l&otilde;ikes 1 toodud kaubaturgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja m&auml;&auml;ratlusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The definition of a fuel or energy undertaking dominating the market complies with the definition of undertaking dominating the market provided for in subsection 13 (1) of the Competition Act (RT I 1998, 30, 410). </inglise>
<eesti>(10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Turgu valitsevas seisundis olev energia tootja v&otilde;ib samaaegselt olla v&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja ja m&uuml;&uuml;a omatoodetud energiat tema valduses oleva v&otilde;rgu kaudu ainult siis, kui puuduvad teised energia tootjad, kes sooviksid m&uuml;&uuml;a energiat sama v&otilde;rgu kaudu, v&otilde;i puuduvad suurtarbijad, kes sooviksid osta energiat sama v&otilde;rgu kaudu m&otilde;nelt teiselt energia tootjalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) An energy producer who dominates the market may simultaneously be a network operator and sell energy produced by the energy producer through the network which is in the possession of the energy producer only if there are no other energy producers who wish to sell energy through the same network, or if there are no large users who wish to purchase energy through the same network from another energy producer. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951; 11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951; 11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (2)) (Kehtetu - 11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (2)) (Repealed - 11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turgu valitsev k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja peab m&uuml;&uuml;ma k&uuml;tust, energiat ja nendega seotud teenuseid Energiaturu Inspektsiooniga koosk&otilde;lastatud hinna ja tariifi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fuel or energy undertaking dominating the market shall sell fuel, energy and related services at prices and rates approved by the Energy Market Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>Energiaturu Inspektsiooniga koosk&otilde;lastatud hinnad ja tariifid koos nendele lisanduvate maksudega avalikustatakse v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud enne nende kehtima hakkamist, ka v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hes &uuml;leriigilise levikuga p&auml;evalehes. </eesti>
<inglise>The prices and rates approved by the Energy Market Inspectorate together with applicable taxes shall be made public not later than six months prior to entry into force thereof, also by publication in at least one national daily newspaper. </inglise>
<eesti>Kuuekuulist avalikustamise n&otilde;uet ei kohaldata hindade ja tariifide alandamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirement to disclose information six months in advance does not apply in the case of reduction of prices and rates. </inglise>
<eesti>Hindade ja tariifide koosk&otilde;lastamise ja avalikustamise n&otilde;uet ei kohaldata energia ja gaasi m&uuml;&uuml;gil suurtarbijatele, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui energiat m&uuml;&uuml;akse lepingu alusel, mille kestus on &uuml;le viie aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirement of approval and publication of prices and rates does not apply to the sale of energy and gas to large users except if energy is sold on the basis of a contract with a term exceeding five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(21.02.2002 j&otilde;ust.12.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 25, 145) </eesti>
<inglise>(21.02.2002 entered into force 12.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 25, 145) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turgu valitsev k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja peab Energiaturu Inspektsiooni n&otilde;udel p&otilde;hjendama rakendatavate hindade ja tariifide moodustumise p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) At the request of the Energy Market Inspectorate, a fuel or energy undertaking dominating the market shall justify the principles applied in setting prices and rates. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kauba v&otilde;i teenuse p&otilde;hjendatud hindade ja tariifide ning muude m&uuml;&uuml;gitingimuste all m&otilde;eldakse m&uuml;&uuml;gitingimusi, mis vastavad ressursside ratsionaalsele kasutamisele, ei sisalda tegevusalade ristsubsideerimist, tagavad energiaettev&otilde;tte vajaliku arengu ja m&otilde;istliku kasumi ning tarbija seaduslikud &otilde;igused k&uuml;tust ja energiat tarbida. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Prices and rates for products and services and other conditions of sale are deemed to be justified if they correspond to the rational use of resources, do not contain cross-subsidisation between areas of activity, and ensure the necessary development of the energy enterprise, reasonable profits and the legal rights of users to use fuel and energy. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Turgu valitseva k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja kauba hinnad ja teenuste tariifid tuleb kujundada selliselt, et oleks tagatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The prices for the products and rates for the services of a fuel or energy undertaking dominating the market shall be established in a manner which ensures: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegevuseks vajalike tootmiskulude katmine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) production costs necessary for activities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeeringud tegevus- ja arenduskohustuse t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) investments for performance of activity and development obligations; </inglise>
<eesti>3) keskkonnakaitsetingimuste t&auml;itmine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) compliance with environmental protection requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kvaliteedi- ja ohutusn&otilde;uete t&auml;itmine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) compliance with quality and safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>5) p&otilde;hjendatud tulukus. </eesti>
<inglise>5) justified profitability. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Turgu valitsev k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tja peab oma raamatupidamises eristama k&uuml;tuse v&otilde;i energia tootmise, edastamise, jaotamise, m&uuml;&uuml;mise ning nendega seotud teenuste osutamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A fuel and energy undertaking dominating the market shall keep separate accounts for the production, transport or transmission, distribution or sale of fuel or energy, and provision of related services. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Turgu valitsev k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja peab Energiaturu Inspektsiooni n&otilde;udel lubama oma raamatupidamise kontrollimist ning andma finantsmajandusliku tegevuse kohta vajalikke selgitusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) At the request of the Energy Market Inspectorate, a fuel or energy undertaking dominating the market shall permit inspection of its accounting and provide necessary explanations regarding its financial and economic activities. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Turgu valitsev k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja esitab igal aastal Energiaturu Inspektsioonile oma majandusaasta auditeeritud aruande kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast majandusaasta l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A fuel or energy undertaking dominating the market shall submit its audited annual report to the Energy Market Inspectorate within six months after the end of each financial year. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Kaubad ja teenused, mille osas ettev&otilde;tja on turgu valitsev, s&auml;testatakse ettev&otilde;tja turuloas. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Products and services in respect of which undertaking has a dominant position on the market shall be specified in the undertaking's market licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) M&uuml;&uuml;jast s&otilde;ltumatute hinnategurite muutumisel v&otilde;ib turgu valitsev k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja korrigeerida kaupade hindu ja teenuste tariife Energiaturu Inspektsiooniga koosk&otilde;lastatud valemi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) Upon a change in price components which are independent of the seller, a fuel or energy undertaking dominating the market may revise the prices of products and rates for services pursuant to a formula approved by the Energy Market Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Elektriv&otilde;rgud </eesti>
<inglise>Power Networks </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektris&uuml;steem </eesti>
<inglise>Power system </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektris&uuml;steem on elektri tootmise, edastamise ja jaotamise tehniline s&uuml;steem, mille moodustavad riigi territooriumil asuvad elektrijaamad, neid &uuml;ksteisega, tarbijatega ning teiste riikide elektris&uuml;steemidega &uuml;hendav elektriv&otilde;rk koos vastavate juhtimis-, kaitse- ja sides&uuml;steemidega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The power system is a technical system for the production, transmission and distribution of electric power comprised of power stations located within the territory of the state, the power network which connects the power stations to one another, users and the power systems of other states, and the corresponding control, protection and communication systems. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektris&uuml;steemi elektriv&otilde;rk koosneb p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rgust ja jaotusv&otilde;rkudest. </eesti>
<inglise>The power network of the power system is comprised of a transmission network and distribution networks. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektris&uuml;steem peab pidevalt toimima &uuml;htse s&uuml;steemina, vastama t&ouml;&ouml;kindluse ja optimaalsuse n&otilde;uetele ning tagama tarbijate katkematu varustamise kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele vastava elektrienergiaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The power system shall operate continuously as a unified system, comply with security and optimality requirements and ensure users an uninterrupted supply of electric power which complies with quality requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elektris&uuml;steemi tehnilist talitlust juhib elektris&uuml;steemi p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tte koosseisus olev juhtimiskeskus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The control centre of the transmission network enterprise of the power system shall manage the technical operations of the power system. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Elektris&uuml;steemi juhtimiskeskus </eesti>
<inglise>Power system control centre </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elektris&uuml;steemi juhtimiskeskus tegutseb k&auml;esolevast seadusest ja teistest &otilde;igusaktidest tulenevate volituste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The power system control centre operates on the basis of the authority arising from this Act and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Elektris&uuml;steemi juhtimiskeskuse poolt k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud volituste piirides antud korraldused on kohustuslikud k&otilde;igile Eesti elektris&uuml;steemi &uuml;hendatud energiaettev&otilde;tjatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Orders issued by the power system control centre that are within the limits of authority prescribed by this Act are binding on all energy undertakings connected to the Estonian power system. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elektris&uuml;steemi juhtimiskeskuse korralduste t&auml;itmisest tulenevate energiaettev&otilde;tjale tekkivate tulude ja kulude arvestuse ja jaotamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted kinnitatakse majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The principles to be applied to the calculation and division of income and expenditure accruing to energy enterprises due to compliance with the orders of the power system control centre shall be approved by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Elektris&uuml;steemi juhtimiskeskus: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The power system control centre shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juhib ja seirab riigi elektris&uuml;steemi &uuml;hendatud elektrijaamade, p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rgu ning jaotusv&otilde;rkude &uuml;hist paralleelt&ouml;&ouml;d, korraldab ja j&auml;lgib l&uuml;limisi ning elektris&uuml;steemis tekkinud h&auml;irete ja avariide k&otilde;rvaldamist p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rgus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) manage and monitor the co-operation of the power stations, transmission network and distribution networks connected to the state power system, organise and supervise switching operations, and eliminate failures and accidents in the transmission network; </inglise>
<eesti>2) koordineerib tehnilist koost&ouml;&ouml;d riigi elektris&uuml;steemiga eritingimustel liitunud tarbijate ja teiste riikide elektris&uuml;steemidega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) co-ordinate technical co-operation with users connected to the state power system under special conditions and with the power systems of other states; </inglise>
<eesti>3) koordineerib elektris&uuml;steemi kaitse- ja automaatikas&uuml;steemide t&ouml;&ouml;d elektrijaamades, -v&otilde;rkudes, p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rgust toidetavate tarbijate juures ning koosk&otilde;lastab kaitse- ja automaatikas&uuml;steemid teiste riikide elektris&uuml;steemidega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) co-ordinate the operation of security systems and automation systems for the power system in power stations and networks, and with regard to users supplied from the transmission network, and harmonise the protection and automation systems with the power systems of other states; </inglise>
<eesti>4) annab korraldusi energiabilansi hoidmisel erakorralistes olukordades tarbimise piiramiseks vastavalt majandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega igal aastal kinnitatavale graafikule. </eesti>
<inglise>4) issue orders to reduce consumption in emergency situations upon maintaining the energy balance pursuant to a schedule annually approved by a regulation of the Minister of Economic Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Elektris&uuml;steemi juhtimiskeskusel on &otilde;igus saada energiaettev&otilde;tjatelt, p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguga &uuml;hendatud suurtarbijatelt ning kohalikult omavalitsuselt andmeid, mis on vajalikud k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja sellest tulenevates &otilde;igusaktides etten&auml;htud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The power system control centre has the right to obtain information from energy undertakings, large users connected to the transmission network and local governments which is necessary for performance of the duties prescribed by this Act and legislation arising therefrom. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Elektris&uuml;steemi juhtimiskeskusel on &otilde;igus v&otilde;tta ettev&otilde;tjalt, kelle elektriseadmed (elektrijaamad, -v&otilde;rgud v&otilde;i nende osad) kuuluvad elektris&uuml;steemi, oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks Energiaturu Inspektsiooniga koosk&otilde;lastatud ja lepingus fikseeritud tingimustel teenustasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The power system control centre has the right to collect a service charge which has been approved by the Energy Market Inspectorate and fixed by contract from undertakings whose power equipment (power stations, networks or parts thereof) is part of the power system. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hiv&otilde;rk </eesti>
<inglise>Transmission network </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&otilde;hiv&otilde;rk on k&otilde;rgepingev&otilde;rk pingega 110 kV ja &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The transmission network is a high voltage network with a voltage of 110 kV or higher. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja, kellele kuulub p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rk, &uuml;lesandeks on &uuml;hendada suuremaid elektri- ja alajaamu &uuml;htseks elektris&uuml;steemiks, mis v&otilde;ib olla &uuml;hendatud teiste riikide p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rkudega, ning edastada elektrienergiat p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguga &uuml;hendatud jaotusv&otilde;rkudele ja tarbijatele. </eesti>
<inglise>A transmission network operator who owns the transmission network is required to connect larger power stations and substations into a unified power system which may be connected to the transmission networks of other states, and transmit electric power to distribution networks and users connected to the transmission network. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettev&otilde;tjad, kelle elektriseadmed on &uuml;hendatud p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguga, s&otilde;lmivad p&otilde;hiv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjaga lepingu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Undertakings whose power equipment is connected to the transmission network shall enter into a contract with the transmission network operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Jaotusv&otilde;rk </eesti>
<inglise>Distribution network </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Jaotusv&otilde;rk on madal- v&otilde;i keskpingev&otilde;rk pingega 110 kV ja alla. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A distribution network is a low or medium voltage network with a voltage of 110 kV or lower. </inglise>
<eesti>Jaotusv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tja, kellele kuulub madal- v&otilde;i keskpingev&otilde;rk, &uuml;lesandeks on tarbijatele elektrienergia jaotamine, m&uuml;&uuml;mine ning elektrienergia jaotamisega seotud teenuste osutamine. </eesti>
<inglise>A distribution network operator who owns a low or medium voltage network is required to distribute and sell electric power to users and to provide services related to the transmission of electric power. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikud, kelle elektriseadmed on &uuml;hendatud jaotusv&otilde;rguga, s&otilde;lmivad jaotusv&otilde;rguettev&otilde;tjaga lepingu, milles m&auml;&auml;ratakse poolte &otilde;igused ja kohustused, elektrienergiahinna ja osutatavate teenuste tariifide m&auml;&auml;ramise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted ning teenuste eest tasumise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons whose power equipment is connected to a distribution network shall enter into a contract with the distribution network operator, which shall determine the rights and obligations of the parties, the principles for determining the price for electric power and rates for the supply of services, and the procedure for payment for services. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalveasutused </eesti>
<inglise>Supervisory authorities </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;tuse- ja energiamajanduse riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostavad: </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision over the fuel and energy sector is exercised by: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the Technical Inspectorate; </inglise>
<eesti>2) Energiaturu Inspektsioon; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the Energy Market Inspectorate; </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&uuml;tuse impordil Tolliamet; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the Customs Board, in the case of import of fuel; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>4) vedelk&uuml;tuse m&uuml;&uuml;gil Tarbijakaitseamet. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the Consumer Protection Board, in the case of sale of liquid fuel. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon </eesti>
<inglise>Technical Inspectorate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioon on Majandusministeeriumi valitsemisalas olev valitsusasutus, kelle p&auml;devusse energeetika valdkonnas kuulub: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Technical Inspectorate is a government agency within the area of government of the Ministry of Economic Affairs, with competence in the energy sector to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaseadmete ning k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaehitiste tehniline ja ohutusalane j&auml;relevalve; </eesti>
<inglise>1) exercise technical and safety supervision over fuel and energy equipment and constructions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951); </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951); </inglise>
<eesti>3) (Kehtetu - 10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951); </eesti>
<inglise>3) (Repealed - 10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951); </inglise>
<eesti>4) tehniliste normide ja standardite v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) draft technical rules and standards; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tehnilist kontrolli vajavate seadmete andmepanga pidamine; </eesti>
<inglise>5) maintain a database of equipment which requires technical inspections; </inglise>
<eesti>6) (Kehtetu - 11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>6) (Repealed - 11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tehnilise J&auml;relevalve Inspektsioonil on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to perform the functions provided for in subsection (1) of this section, the Technical Inspectorate has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) saada energia- ja k&uuml;tuseettev&otilde;tjatelt ning energia- ja k&uuml;tuseseadmete projekteerijatelt, valmistajatelt, paigaldajatelt, ehitajatelt, hooldajatelt, remontijatelt ja tarnijatelt andmeid, mis on vajalikud k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) obtain information which is necessary for performance of the functions provided for in this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof from energy and fuel undertakings and persons who design, manufacture, install, construct, maintain, repair or supply fuel and energy equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teha oma p&auml;devuse piires kohustuslikke ettekirjutusi k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide s&auml;tete rikkumise l&otilde;petamiseks ja rikkumisega tekitatud tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) issue mandatory precepts, within the limits of its competence, to cease a violation of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof and to eliminate the consequences of such violation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) keelata &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud ohutusn&otilde;uetele mittevastavate energia- ja k&uuml;tuseseadmete paigaldamine ja tarnimine ning ohtlike seadmete kasutamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) prohibit the installation or supply of energy and fuel equipment which is not in compliance with the safety requirements provided for in legislation, and the use of dangerous equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&auml;&auml;rata k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides etten&auml;htud karistusi; </eesti>
<inglise>4) impose the punishments prescribed by this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>5) esindada Eesti Vabariiki &otilde;igusaktidega etten&auml;htud korras rahvusvahelistes organisatsioonides ning teha koost&ouml;&ouml;d v&auml;lisriikide tehnilise j&auml;relevalve asutustega. </eesti>
<inglise>5) represent the Republic of Estonia in international organisations pursuant to the procedure prescribed by legislation, and co-operate with the technical supervisory authorities of other states. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Energiaturu Inspektsioon </eesti>
<inglise>Energy Market Inspectorate </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel moodustatav Energiaturu Inspektsioon on Majandusministeeriumi valitsemisalas olev valitsusasutus, kelle p&auml;devusse kuulub: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Energy Market Inspectorate formed on the basis of this Act is a government agency within the area of government of the Ministry of Economic Affairs, with competence to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaturu j&auml;relevalve; </eesti>
<inglise>1) supervise the fuel and energy markets; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tjatele turulubade v&auml;ljastamine, j&auml;relevalve loa tingimuste j&auml;rgimise &uuml;le ja loa kehtetuks tunnistamine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) issue, supervise compliance with and revoke fuel and energy market licences; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>3) turgu valitsevate k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tjate majandustulemuste kontrollimine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) review the financial performance of fuel and energy undertakings dominating the market; </inglise>
<eesti>4) konkurentsi tekitamisele kaasaaitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) foster competition; </inglise>
<eesti>5) turgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja poolt m&uuml;&uuml;dava k&uuml;tuse, energia ja nendega seotud teenuste hindade kontrollimine ja koosk&otilde;lastamine; </eesti>
<inglise>5) review and approve the prices of fuel and energy sold and of related services provided by enterprises dominating the market; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>6) liitumistasude ja liitumislepingu tingimuste kontrollimine; </eesti>
<inglise>6) review connection charges and the terms and conditions of connection contracts; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>7) k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tjate tegutsemis- ja arenduskohustuse kontrollimine; </eesti>
<inglise>7) monitor compliance by fuel and energy undertakings with their activity and development obligations; </inglise>
<eesti>8) m&uuml;&uuml;dava k&uuml;tuse ja energia kvaliteedi kontrollimine; </eesti>
<inglise>8) monitor the quality of fuel and energy being sold; </inglise>
<eesti>9) koost&ouml;&ouml; tegemine tarbijakaitse&uuml;hingutega ja neile tarbijakaitseseadusega (RT I 1994, 2, 13; RT I 1999, 35, 450; 102, 907; 2000, 40, 252; 59, 379; 2001, 50, 283 ja 289; 56, 332; 2002, 18, 97) antud &otilde;iguste realiseerimise v&otilde;imaldamine energeetika vallas. </eesti>
<inglise>9) co-operate with consumer protection associations and facilitate exercise of the rights granted to such associations by the Consumer Protection Act (RT I 1994, 2, 13; RT I 1999, 35, 450; 102, 907; 2000, 40, 252; 59, 379; 2001, 50, 283 and 289; 56, 332; 2002, 18, 97) in the energy sector. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks on Energiaturu Inspektsioonil &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to perform its functions, the Energy Market Inspectorate has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) saada k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tjatelt andmeid, mis on vajalikud k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) obtain information which is necessary for performance of the functions provided for in this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof from energy and fuel undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) korraldada energiaettev&otilde;tjate omavahelist koost&ouml;&ouml;d energia- ja keskkonnas&auml;&auml;stlikuks tegevuseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) organise co-operation among energy undertakings for conservation of energy and the environment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks turgu valitsevate k&uuml;tuse- ja energiaettev&otilde;tjate poolt rakendatav hinnakujundamine k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 42 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) determine the pricing principles to be implemented by fuel and energy undertakings dominating the market in the circumstances provided for in subsection 42 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koosk&otilde;lastada turgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja poolt m&uuml;&uuml;dava k&uuml;tuse ja energia hindu ning teenuste tariife vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ikele 2 ning edastamistariife vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ikele 7 ja kinnitada elektrienergia hinnad vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 (1) l&otilde;ikele 2; </eesti>
<inglise>4) approve the prices and rates for fuel, energy and services sold by undertakings dominating the market in accordance with subsection 19 (2) of this Act and transmission and transport rates in accordance with subsection 15 (7) of this Act and confirm the prices of electric power in accordance with subsection 28 (1) (2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </inglise>
<eesti>4 (1)) teha oma p&auml;devuse piires kohustuslikke ettekirjutusi; </eesti>
<inglise>4 (1)) issue mandatory precepts within its competence; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 60, 951) </inglise>
<eesti>5) kehtestada k&uuml;tuse v&otilde;i energia ajutine edastamis- v&otilde;i jaotamistasu mitte kauemaks kui kaheks kuuks olukorras, kus edastamis- v&otilde;i jaotamistasud ei ole p&otilde;hjendatud ning k&uuml;tuse- v&otilde;i energiaettev&otilde;tja ei j&auml;rgi Energiaturu Inspektsiooni poolt tehtud ettekirjutust; </eesti>
<inglise>5) establish a temporary fee for fuel or energy transport, transmission or distribution for no longer than two months in the event that transport, transmission or distribution fees are not justified and the fuel or energy undertaking does not comply with precepts issued by the Energy Market Inspectorate; </inglise>
<eesti>6) esindada Eestit &otilde;igusaktidega etten&auml;htud korras rahvusvahelistes organisatsioonides ning teha koost&ouml;&ouml;d v&auml;lisriikide energiaturuasutustega; </eesti>
<inglise>6) represent Estonia in international organisations pursuant to the procedure prescribed by legislation and co-operate with the energy market authorities of other states; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kohaldada k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453; 87, 524 ja 526; 97, 605; 102, 677; 2002, 18, 98; 21, 117) etten&auml;htud karistust. </eesti>
<inglise>7) impose the punishments prescribed by this Act and in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453; 87, 524 and 526; 97, 605; 102, 677; 2002, 18, 98; 21, 117). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Tolliamet </eesti>
<inglise>Customs Board </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevast seadusest l&auml;htuvalt kuulub Tolliameti p&auml;devusse: </eesti>
<inglise>Pursuant to this Act, the Customs Board is competent to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&uuml;tuse impordil turuloa kontrollimine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) examine the market licence upon the import of fuel; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vedelk&uuml;tuse impordil turuloa ja vedelk&uuml;tuse vastavussertifikaadi kontrollimine ning vedelk&uuml;tuse vastavuse kontrollimine kehtestatud kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>2) examine the market licence and the certificate of conformity of liquid fuel and to verify conformity of liquid fuel with the established quality requirements upon the import of liquid fuel. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 239) </eesti>
